Description:\
\
In this project I will study patterns in transportation using data from New York City taxi trips available at http://chriswhong.com/open-data/foil_nyc_taxi/. The goal is to provide actionable information to make the day of a taxi driver more efficient in terms of making more money while driving less and make the working day more predictable. This information will help drivers and taxi agents to make informed decision on where to be (or go) at a specific time.\
\
Initially I will make a study of correlations between different quantities, such as time of trip, distance, time of pick-up, location of pick-up, fare. Two plots have been provided, to provide concrete insight into the feasibility of this project, that show how the mean traveled distance depends on the pick-up time on a typical day (https://goo.gl/photos/A8QKKB11qjGQEMAy9) and a time series of the fraction of trips starting at two NYC neighborhoods of equal area (one within Chelsea and the other in midtown) throughout a typical day (
