\
At the end of this project, I will provide a tool, that I call a \'93decision map,\'94 so that, given the current location of a taxi, the driver can determine (according to the driver\'92s constrains) where to drive in order to maximize the chance for a desired outcome. Outcomes might be a specific drop-off location for the next trip, fare amount, time travel or a combination of those. This tool will be able to answer questions such as, given the current position of the taxi, in which direction should the taxi go to increase the chances to pick up a passenger that will travel in a specific direction, and a given distance or, given a starting working time, to what locations should the taxi go to maximize the changes of collecting a specific amount of money at the end of the day.\
\
I believe this kind of information will improve the working experience of taxi drivers and agents by increasing predictability. Although taxis are highly regulated in NYC (for example, drivers cannot pick up more people while there is a passenger in the taxi), it will also provide a tool for competing with modern, more unregulated, transportations systems, such as Uber. In addition, improving efficiency will allow for drivers to spend less gas and, in turn, have positive implications to environmental conservation.\
